'''Sharon Newman''' ([[Name at birth|n<U+00E9>e]] '''Collins'''; formerly '''Abbott''') is a fictional character from the American [[CBS Daytime]] soap opera ''[[The Young and the Restless]]'', portrayed by [[Sharon Case]]. Created by [[William J. Bell]] as a [[love interest]] for [[Nicholas Newman]] ([[Joshua Morrow]]), the character made her onscreen debut on March 24, 1994. Before Case permanently took over the role, Sharon was briefly portrayed by [[Monica Potter]] and [[Heidi Mark]], who each played the role for two months. When first introduced, the character was described as a "young girl from the poor side of town". Nick and Sharon were quickly married and had a son, [[Noah Newman|Noah]] ([[Robert Adamson (actor)|Robert Adamson]]), and they later gained custody of [[Cassie Newman|Cassie]] ([[Camryn Grimes]]); the baby Sharon had as a teenager, who she gave up for adoption. The marriage faced countless problems, including infidelities on both sides. Following Cassie's death as a result of a car crash, Nick cheated on Sharon with [[Phyllis Summers]] ([[Michelle Stafford]]), resulting in a pregnancy that ultimately ended Nick and Sharon's 11-year marriage. 

Despite her marriage and subsequent divorce to [[Jack Abbott (The Young and the Restless)|Jack Abbott]] ([[Peter Bergman]]), Nick and Sharon had an affair and conceived a third child, [[Faith Newman]] (Alyvia Alyn Lind). During her pregnancy, Sharon experienced [[kleptomania]]. Faith was kidnapped by [[Adam Newman]] ([[Michael Muhney]]), Nick's brother, leaving Sharon to believe she had died. Sharon then began a relationship with Adam, which led to a brief marriage. Even when Adam's actions were revealed and Faith was returned to Nick and Sharon, she remained in love with him; Case called the pairing surprising, while [[SoapNet]] penned the relationship "dark".<ref name="e"/><ref name="dark"/> 

During head writer and executive producer [[Maria Arena Bell]]'s tenure on the show, the character's storyline changed in direction. In 2011, she was presumed dead and escaped from prison after being falsely sentenced for the murder of [[List of The Young and the Restless characters (2008)#Skye Lockhart Newman|Skye Newman]] (Laura Stone). The following year, Sharon had a romantic relationship with her ex father-in-law, [[Victor Newman]] ([[Eric Braeden]]), which Case labelled [[incest]]uous. This was followed by a plot which saw Sharon manipulatively gain control over his company, Newman Enterprises, while he was missing. The once "beloved" character was then widely received as "crazy", with critics blaming Bell for the character's "royal destruction", "via one ill-conceived storyline and/or romance after another", amid vows to make Sharon stronger.<ref name="ra"/><ref name="MABCritic"/> Bell was fired, and replaced with [[Josh Griffith]] who vowed to rebuild the character,<ref name=rebuild/> which led to Sharon being diagnosed with [[bipolar disorder]], explaining her out of character behavior.<ref name="Eppie"/>

Sharon has been characterized as "kindhearted", but also "insecure" and "not your typical romantic lead".<ref name=tvsoap /> Despite crimes and faults, the character is described as a central heroine<ref name="heroine"/> and has been called soap opera's "hottest mess".<ref name=suicide/> The [[supercouple]] pairing of [[Nicholas Newman and Sharon Collins|Nick and Sharon]], dubbed as "Shick" by viewers, has garnered a large fan following. Case has became popular with viewers, gathering multiple awards and nominations including two [[Soap Opera Digest Awards]] and the [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress]] in 1999, among five other Daytime Emmy nominations. Case' performance has received general praise from critics, with many praising her for withstanding Bell's heavily panned storylines.

== Casting ==
[[File:Monica Potter.jpg|thumb|right|170px|[[Monica Potter]] originated the role of Sharon, but vacated it shortly after.]]
Sharon was introduced and created by [[William J. Bell]], with the character making her first appearance on March 24, 1994.<ref name="24march">{{Cite episode |title=Episode #1.5350|series= The Young and the Restless |serieslink=The Young and the Restless|network=CBS |airdate=March 24, 1994}}</ref> Case, who plays Sharon to the present day,<ref>{{cite web|title=Sharon Case|url=http://www.cbs.com/shows/the_young_and_the_restless/cast/61676|work=The Young and the Restless|publisher=CBS|accessdate=November 16, 2012}}</ref> became the third actress to hold the part in a four-month span.<ref>{{cite web|last=Novakovich|first=Lilana|title=Case steps into Y&R Role|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/497293231.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Mar+03%2C+1995&author=Lilana+Novakovich&pub=Waterloo+Region+Record&desc=Sharon+Case+steps+into+Y%26R+role&pqatl=google|work=[[Waterloo Region Record|The Record]]|publisher=[[Metroland Media Group]]|date=March 3, 1995|accessdate=November 16, 2012}}</ref> [[Monica Potter]] was the first actress to portray Sharon, followed by [[Heidi Mark]], with each actress having a two-month stint.<ref>{{cite news|last=Elias|first=Justine|title=The new season/film: up and coming: Monica Potter; an early lesson in self-confidence pays off|url=http://www.nytimes.com/1998/09/13/movies/new-season-film-up-coming-monica-potter-early-lesson-self-confidence-pays-off.html|accessdate=November 16, 2012|newspaper=[[New York Times]]|date=September 13, 1998}}</ref> Case had previously worked on ''[[General Hospital]]'' and ''[[As The World Turns]]'' when cast in August 1994 for the role.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sharon Case bio|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/sharon-case-bio|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=[[Source Interlink]]|accessdate=November 16, 2012}}</ref><ref name="august">{{cite news|title=Salem's lives brace for new trouble|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=PrY0AAAAIBAJ&sjid=mT8DAAAAIBAJ&pg=6242,6124077&dq=heidi+mark+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|accessdate=November 16, 2012|newspaper=Walker Country Messenger Plus|date=July 26, 1994}}</ref> She believed that she would only be playing Sharon for a maximum of six months.<ref>{{cite news|last=Novakovich|first=Lilana|title=A Case for not settling down; Y&R star has been around and doesn't count on anything|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/432598141.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jan+26%2C+2001&author=Lilana+Novakovich&pub=Waterloo+Region+Record&desc=A+Case+for+not+settling+down%3B+Y%26R+star+has+been+around+and+doesn't+count+on+anything&pqatl=google|accessdate=November 16, 2012|newspaper=[[The Record (Waterloo Region)|The Record]]|publisher=[[Metroland Media Group]]|date=January 26, 2001}}</ref> In 2003, the actress briefly departed due to contract negotiations which were resolved that April, when she inked a new deal with the producers, after being off-screen from February 17 to May 1.<ref name="contract">{{cite web|last=Kroll|first=Dan|url=http://www.soapcentral.com/yr/news/2003/0310-case_woodland.php|title=New Contracts Keep Case, Woodland With Y&R|work=Soapcentral.com|date=March 5, 2003|accessdate=November 18, 2012}}</ref><ref name="Deal">{{cite news|last=Goldstein|first=Toby|title=Case re-signs with Restless|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=8-odAAAAIBAJ&sjid=MsgEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6250,462797&dq=sharon+case+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|accessdate=November 16, 2012|newspaper=[[TimesDaily]]|date=April 3, 2003}}</ref>

== Character development ==

===Characterization===
Sharon, a "young girl from the poor side of town", has developed into a mother and businesswoman.<ref name="Character Bio - Sharon Abbott">{{cite web|title=Character Bio <U+2013> Sharon Abbott|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/about/characters/sharon-newman.php|publisher=[[Sony Entertainment Television]]|accessdate=December 22, 2011}}</ref> Nekeeta Borden of [[Zap2It]] described her as "kind-hearted" and a "she-ro"{{what}} who was a "ravishing beauty" who wanted to start "her own trends" rather than follow other members of the Newman family.<ref>{{cite web|last=Borden|first=Nekeeta|title=Who Needs Characterization on The Young and the Restless?|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2010/12/02/who-needs-characterization-on-the-young-and-the-restless?page=0,4|work=[[Zap2It]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=December 4, 2012|page=4|date=December 2, 2010}}</ref> According to Case, Sharon does "weird things and panics" due to stress, and her mistakes "eat away at her".<ref name=tvca>{{cite web|last=Branco|first=Nelson|title=Interview with Y&R's Sharon Case|work=[[TV Guide|TV Guide Canada]]|publisher=[[Lions Gate Entertainment]]|date=April 8, 2010}}</ref><ref name="f">{{cite web|url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/the-young-and-the-restless/the-sharon-case-interview-the-young-and-the-restless/2009/02/25/|title=The Sharon Case Interview <U+2013> The Young and the Restless|work=Michael Fairman |publisher=On-Air On-Soaps|date=February 25, 2009|accessdate=November 18, 2010|first=Michael|last=Fairman}}</ref><ref name="g">{{cite news|last=Havens|first=Candace|title=Sharon Case is truly Young and Restless|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=XPFPAAAAIBAJ&sjid=wQgEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6219,2862555&dq=sharon+case+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|accessdate=December 24, 2011|newspaper=[[Star-Banner]]|publisher=[[Halifax Media Group]]|date=June 4, 2002}}</ref> Case described Sharon as "insecure", telling the ''[[Star-Banner]]'' that she didn't feel good enough to "have a happy relationship with a man" but has come a long way despite "slip-ups along the way".<ref name="g"/> She further stated: "Sharon goes through many emotions in a week. On Monday she may be in a romantic mood and setting up some wonderful dinner for Nick. On Wednesday, she could be comforting a friend who is going through a tough time, and then by Friday one of her children may be sick and she fears it's the end of the world. But it's all fun".<ref name="g"/> The character was described as a "bitch" following a storyline which saw her take over Newman Enterprises in 2012.<ref name="MSN" />

Case wears her own line of [[Pomp Jewelry]] while playing the character,<ref>{{cite web|title=Sharon Case Chats About Jewelry Line|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/specials/interviews_detail_5594.html|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20100727181618/http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/specials/interviews_detail_5594.html|archivedate=July 27, 2010|work=[[Sony Entertainment Television]]|publisher=The Young and the Restless|accessdate=January 18, 2012}}</ref> and has opinionated that Sharon's career should be that of a fashion designer, "I have a lot of great stories on ''Y&R'' so it<U+2019>s not like I<U+2019>m unhappy or think I need more story but if ''Y&R'' wanted to go in that direction with her, in terms of her career, I think it would make sense".<ref name=tvca /> Of the writing for the character, Case said that she couldn't do what she does without it; "They both have to be there. I couldn't have gotten away with this without those lines".<ref name=SOU>{{cite web|last=Branco|first=Nelson|title=Y&R<U+2019>s Sharon Case Chats On Campy Sharon Newman, Shiktor & Eric Braeden<U+2019>s Comments on Twitter Drama!|url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/news/yrs-sharon-case-chats-on-campy-sharon-newman-shiktor-eric-braedens-comments-on-twitter-drama/2012/08/31/|work=Soap Opera Uncensored|publisher=Michael Fairman|accessdate=October 1, 2012|date=August 31, 2012}}</ref> The actress has expressed displeasure with Sharon being "paired with too many men" because it "waters her down", wanting to integrate different sides of Sharon in her performance.<ref name=SOU/>

===Relationship with Nick Newman===
{{Main|Nick and Sharon}} 
[[File:Shick Wedding.jpg|thumb|left|upright|185px|Nick and Sharon at their wedding, February 1996]]

Sharon has been romantically linked to her high school sweetheart [[Nicholas Newman|Nicholas "Nick" Newman]] ([[Joshua Morrow]]) since her beginning on the series. As teenagers, they dream of eloping,<ref name="h">{{cite news|title=Soap Opera Updates|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=Y05OAAAAIBAJ&sjid=KxUEAAAAIBAJ&pg=1290,170359&dq=nick+and+sharon+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|accessdate=December 24, 2011|newspaper=[[Star-News]]|publisher=[[Halifax Media Group]]|date=October 1, 1995}}</ref> and face their first major hurdle when Sharon's ex-boyfriend [[Matt Clark (The Young and the Restless)|Matt Clark]] ([[Eddie Cibrian]]) exposes the fact that Sharon had a child with her former boyfriend in Madison, which she gave up for adoption. Nick believed she was a virgin and briefly breaks up with Sharon, although they soon reunite.<ref name="Virginal">{{cite news|title=Speaking of Soaps: Lorna seeks support on "Another World"|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=F-RNAAAAIBAJ&sjid=Df0DAAAAIBAJ&pg=2966,144372&dq=nick+and+sharon+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|accessdate=December 24, 2011|newspaper=[[The Ledger|Lakeland Ledger]]|publisher=[[Halifax Media Group]]|date=July 1, 1995}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sally shot; Luke, Laura reunite|publisher=([[South Florida Sun-Sentinel]] Fort Lauderdale)|author=Lynda Hirsch (Special to the Sun-Sentinel)|page=4|date=July 13, 1995}}</ref> With Matt behind them, they marry in February 1996, and have their first child [[Noah Newman|Noah]] ([[Robert Adamson (actor)|Robert Adamson]]) in 1997, the same year Sharon was reunited with the daughter she gave up for adoption, Cassie ([[Camryn Grimes]]). Sharon's best friend [[Grace Turner]] ([[Jennifer Gareis]]) schemes to have Nick for herself,<ref name=sos>{{cite web|title=Speaking Of Soaps|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=809IAAAAIBAJ&sjid=MP0DAAAAIBAJ&pg=5361,176552&dq=nick+and+sharon+grace+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|work=[[Lakeland Ledger]]|publisher=[[Halifax Media Group]]|author=Mary Ann Cooper|accessdate=January 27, 2012|date=July 11, 1998}}</ref> and Nick cheats on Sharon with her multiple times, leading to another break-up.<ref name=sos /><ref name=sos2>{{cite web|title=Speaking Of Soaps|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=R05IAAAAIBAJ&sjid=Rv0DAAAAIBAJ&pg=5122,5110350&dq=nick+and+sharon+grace+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|work=[[Lakeland Ledger]]|publisher=[[Halifax Media Group]]|accessdate=January 18, 2012|author=Mary Ann Cooper|date=October 17, 1998}}</ref> They re-connect during a custody battle for Cassie. Of their highly anticipated reunion, then-head writer [[Kay Alden]] noted that in the last several months "there's been a lot of stop-and-go" and "mixed messages" between the couple, but their feelings were "definitely clear" again.<ref name="Sealed with a Kiss!">{{cite book|chapter=Sealed With A Kiss! |title=[[Soap Opera Digest]] |publisher=[[American Media, Inc.]] |pages=23<U+2013>25 |date=June 29, 1999}}</ref> Morrow also felt that Nick loved Cassie as his daughter, just as much as he loves Noah.<ref name="Sealed with a Kiss!" /> Sharon herself eventually cheats by sleeping with [[Diego Guittierez]] ([[Greg Vaughan]]).<ref>{{cite web|title=Soaps: A synopsis of this weeks afternoon dramas|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=zFouAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ZdoFAAAAIBAJ&pg=6871,4300381&dq=nick+diego+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|work=[[The Item]]|publisher=Osteen Publishing Co.|accessdate=January 28, 2012|date=March 30, 2002}}</ref> In May 2005, fourteen year-old Cassie is killed in a car accident. Nick becomes distant and cheats on Sharon with [[Phyllis Summers]] ([[Michelle Stafford]]). The marriage ends the following year when Nick moves on with a pregnant Phyllis, who gives birth to their daughter [[Summer Newman]].<ref name="entertainment1.sympatico">{{cite web|first=Nelson|last=Branco|title=The stories, the stars, and the big blunders that shaped one fantastic year! | work=[[TV Guide]]| url=http://entertainment1.sympatico.msn.ca/2006+Soaps+Yearbook/TV_Guide/Soaps/Features/Articles/211206_bestworst_NB.htm?isfa=1| archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20070916192535/http://entertainment1.sympatico.msn.ca/2006+Soaps+Yearbook/TV_Guide/Soaps/Features/Articles/211206_bestworst_NB.htm?isfa=1| archivedate=September 16, 2007|date=November 26, 2006|accessdate=June 9, 2007}}</ref>

Although Sharon moved on by marrying [[Jack Abbott (The Young and the Restless)|Jack Abbott]] ([[Peter Bergman]]), Nick and Sharon remain in love. They share kiss while Nick is an amnesiac and believes they are still married; Phyllis becomes extremely jealous of Sharon, insulting her in a published article in her magazine ''Restless Style''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hinsey|first=Carolyn|title='Y&R's' Phyllis doesn't like Sharon her man|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/television/y-phyllis-sharon-man-article-1.247617|work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]]|publisher=[[Mortimer Zuckerman]]|accessdate=December 24, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless: Week In Review 10/8-10/12|url=http://www.buddytv.com/articles/the-young-and-the-restless/the-young-and-the-restless-wee-12369.aspx|work=[[Buddy TV]]|publisher=([[Source Interlink]])|accessdate=January 28, 2012|date=October 12, 2007}}</ref><ref name=ndn>{{cite web|title=Phyllis writes off Sharon on 'The Young and the Restless'|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2008-10-03/entertainment/17908993_1_phyllis-sharon-michelle-stafford|work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]]|publisher=[[Mortimer Zuckerman]]|accessdate=January 28, 2012|author=Carolyn Hinsey|date=October 3, 2008}}</ref> In January 2009, "first loves" Nick and Sharon reunite and make love at the Abbott cabin, an affair that was "much anticipated" by viewers according to [[SoapNet]].<ref name="447W" /> According to Case, Sharon wanted Nick "more than anyone" but only if he left Phyllis,<ref name="b">{{cite web|last=Hinsey|first=Carolyn (daily news staff writer)|title=Sharon kissed in the Nick of time on 'Young & the Restless'|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2009-05-29/entertainment/17922199_1_sharon-case-phyllis-kisses|publisher=[[Mortimer Zuckerman]]|work=[[Daily News (New York)|Daily News]]|accessdate=December 22, 2011}}</ref> while Morrow told ''[[TV Guide]]'' that although the reunion was "messy", fans "wanted this for a long time".<ref>{{cite web|last=Bowe|first=Jillian|title=Shick Does the Sheet Shimmy on The Young and the Restless|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2009/01/shick-does-the-sheet-shimmy-on-the-young-and-the-restless|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=July 13, 2012|date=January 20, 2009}}</ref> After another [[one night stand]], Sharon becomes pregnant<ref name="Reu">{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless 2009|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/episode-info/yearly/?year=2009|publisher=[[Sony Entertainment Television]]|accessdate=November 13, 2012}}</ref> and briefly lies about Jack being the baby's father after Summer falls ill and Phyllis needs Nick.<ref name="Reu"/> Nick soon finds out, but their daughter Faith is kidnapped at birth by Nick's brother Adam and given to Ashley, Jack's sister. Sharon believes Faith had died, and romanced  a guilty Adam.<ref name="Reu" /> Faith is eventually reunited with her parents, and Adam's crimes are revealed.<ref name="2010For" /> Nick and Sharon are reunited and are engaged briefly that November, but break up when she sleeps with Adam.<ref name="2010For">{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless 2010|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/episode-info/yearly/?year=2010|publisher=[[Sony Entertainment Television]]|accessdate=November 13, 2012}}</ref> The relationship between Nick and Sharon became bitter afterwards.<ref name="i">{{cite web|title=Young and Restless Recaps <U+2014> Y&R Week of December 6, 2010|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/yr-week-december-6-2010|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=[[American Media (publisher)|American Media]]|accessdate=December 28, 2011}}</ref> Since, both Case and Morrow have confessed that although the couple won't "ever be over" and "belong together", they aren't together now and may not reunite "anytime soon".<ref name="e" /><ref name="Saint Nick">{{cite book|last=McElwain |first=Julie |chapter=Saint Nick |title=CBS Soaps In Depth |pages=55<U+2013>57 |date=September 10, 2012}}</ref>

===Cameron Kirsten ordeal===
[[File:Sharon and Cameron's dead body.png|thumb|right|175px|In disbelief, Sharon views the dead body of Frank Barritt, while believing it to be that of Cameron Kirsten (2004).]]
{{quote box
|width = 18em
|border = 1px
|align=left
|bgcolor= LightCyan
|fontsize = 88%
|quote = "You have to have people doing bad things or what type of story are you going to have?"<ref name=tvsoap />
|salign = right
|source =<U+2014>Case on the storyline (2004)}}
In February 2003, Case temporarily exited the show as a result of lengthy contract negotiations.<ref name="contract"/> Instead of having the character depart fully or be killed off, executive producer at the time [[David Shaughnessy]] chose to have her leave town.<ref name=tvsoap /> While away, Sharon became depressed and on the verge of suicide.<ref name=tvsoap>{{cite news|last=Fairman|first=Michael|title=Sharon Case reveals how her sweet, demure character became a murderer|newspaper=Australia's No1 TV Soap|date=September 20, 2004|pages=23<U+2013>24}}</ref> Case explained that her life had "fallen apart" and she initially left town to commit suicide, drinking herself into "a complete stupor". That night, she met and had an affair with businessman [[Cameron Kirsten]] ([[Linden Ashby]]), who ended up physically abusing her.<ref name=tvsoap /> In April, Case re-signed her contract with the show.<ref name="Deal" /> Upon Sharon's return to Genoa City, she is horrified when Cameron follows her for supposed "business" with Newman Enterprises.<ref name=tvsoap2>{{cite news|last=Chegwidden|first=Yvette|title=Psychopath Haunts Sharon|newspaper=Australia's No1 TV Soap|date= September 20, 2004|page=5}}</ref> He blackmails her into hooking up with him at a motel. She shows up, and they end up in a physical altercation which ends when Sharon throws a bottle at him to prevent him from raping her, "killing" him.<ref name=tvsoap2 /> She drives around with his dead body in her car trunk for days and dumps it in an ally.<ref name=tvsoap2 /> Sharon's former best-friend and enemy Grace returns to town and discovers Cameron alive, nursing him to health. Detective Weber ([[Sherman Augustus]]) becomes suspicious towards Sharon for Cameron's disappearance. Sharon begins "hallucinating" with visions of Cameron's "ghost", which later turns out to be him in the flesh.<ref name=tvsoap2 /><ref name=daytimetv>{{cite news|title=Murder Mystery: Sharon meets a living corpse|newspaper=Daytime TV|date=October 2004|pages=32<U+2013>33}}</ref> Case noted that she was getting in "deeper" trouble by making several mistakes as a result of her "trying to do the right thing".<ref name=tvsoap /> 

Cameron eventually reveals himself while Sharon is having lunch with Nikki. He had murdered Sharon's ex (and Cassie's biological father) [[List of The Young and the Restless characters (2000s)#Frank Barritt|Frank Barritt]] (Phil Dozois), who was visiting town, and put his body in Sharon's trunk.<ref name=tvsoap2 /> Soon, Cameron's crimes are revealed and he is jailed, leaving Sharon free to her normal life.<ref name=tvsoap2 /> Although Sharon didn't actually "murder" Cameron, Case praised the storyline and stated that Sharon was still a heroine. She also felt that Sharon was still a romantic lead, noting that "Your romantic lead shouldn't just be a simple romantic lead. Sharon was that for a long time. She was in this love story with Nick and nothing really happened to her. You can only carry that so far."<ref name=tvsoap />

=== Cassie's death ===
In 2005, "good girl" Cassie develops into a "rebellious" teenager, with Nick and Sharon having a rough time dealing with her acting out.<ref name="AboutCassieD">{{cite web|last=Kontranowski|first=Liberty|title=Y&R Do You Remember?: Cassie Newman's Death|url=http://soaps.about.com/od/showoverviews/a/CassieDeathYR.htm|work=[[About.com{{!}}About]]|accessdate=December 7, 2012}}</ref>  Cassie develops a crush on "bad-boy" [[Daniel Romalotti]] ([[Michael Graziadei]]), who is dating [[Lily Winters]] ([[Christel Khalil]]). One night, against her parent's wishes, she sneaks out to a party. In a ploy to impress a drunken Daniel, she attempts to drive him home, despite being underage. However, in "true soap style", the car she is driving crashes, leaving them with no recollection of the event. Daniel was thought to be driving, and blamed for the accident. A weak Cassie escapes from the hospital to find Daniel and tell him she was driving, right before being brought back to the hospital.<ref name="AboutCassieD" /> During the episode that aired May 24, Cassie passes away with Nick and Sharon by her side.<ref name="SSN">{{cite web|last=Mistretta|first=Amy|title=Throwback Thursday Y&R Poll: Cassie's Death.|url=http://soaps.sheknows.com/youngandrestless/news/id/29329/|work=She Knows Soaps|publisher=She Knows Entertainment|accessdate=December 7, 2012|date=November 15, 2012}}</ref> Grimes said she didn't think Cassie would die, but if it was "meant to happen, it's meant to happen". She recalled filming her last scenes with Case and Morrow "ridiculously hard".<ref name="CassieCrying">{{cite web|url=http://soaps.sheknows.com/youngandrestless/news/id/4061/The_Young_and_the_Restless_Soapscom_Catches_Up_wit/ |title=The Young and the Restless: Soaps.com Catches Up with Camryn Grimes! - The Young and the Restless News - Soaps.com |publisher=Soaps.sheknows.com |date= |accessdate=2012-12-02}}</ref> Daniel is cleared of all charges; Nick and Sharon begin Cassie's Foundation, a movement to prevent teenage [[drinking and driving]].<ref name="AboutCassieD" /> According to Case, whenever Sharon loses something in her life, it "reminds her and reactivates Cassie<U+2019>s death for her." After Nick cheats on Sharon following Cassie's death, Case said it "makes you so fearful that you are going to be alone for the rest of your life; that no matter what you go out in life to create, it<U+2019>s going to be ruined anyway." Additionally, the actress opined that Sharon lost her identity after Cassie's death.<ref name="f" /> In 2012, during a court-battle over the family company, Newman Enterprises, Nick tells a judge that Sharon's mental problems date back to after they lost Cassie. Luke Kerr of [[Zap2it]] called this playing the "Cassie card".<ref>{{cite web|last=Kerr|first=Luke|title=Nick Plays the Cassie Card on Y&R; GH<U+2019>s One Percent Club Tries to Save Port Charles|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/09/06/soap-bytes-nick-plays-the-cassie-card-against-sharon-on-yr-gh%E2%80%99s-one-percent-club-tries-to|work=[[Zap2it]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=December 8, 2012|date=September 7, 2012}}</ref>

===Other romances ===
According to Case, Sharon loses her "entire identity" after Nick cheats on her, and "needed a new one".<ref name="f" /> She develops a romance with [[Jack Abbott]] ([[Peter Bergman]]), Phyllis' ex.<ref name="Peter06" /> Bergman called the courtship "only appropriate", explaining: "Wherever Sharon goes, she is embarrassed. Will Phyllis come walking around the corner? But Sharon doesn't have any reason to be embarrassed with Jack."<ref name="Peter06">{{cite web|title='The Young and the Restless' - The gloves are off: Jack is back!|url=http://jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20060909/ent/ent4.html|work=[[Jamaica Gleaner]]|publisher=[[Gleaner Company]]|accessdate=November 22, 2012|date=September 9, 2006}}</ref> They marry in April 2007,<ref name="SCC" /> with Case praising the marriage as an "awesome representation of modern marriage" which depicted every day problems married couples face including dishonesty and how it "whittles away at the marriage".<ref name="f" /> Within two years, Jack's constant lies end the marriage, as Sharon couldn't deal with his "broken promises again and again", which led to a divorce in April 2009.<ref name="f" /><ref name="SCC" /> Before Jack entered her life, Sharon had an affair with [[Brad Carlton]] ([[Don Diamont]]) years earlier, though their romance was never fully explored.<ref name="SCC" /> Case felt that Brad and Sharon should have been together after she divorced Jack, stating that the characters could have had "this very cool, ''[[Mr. and Mrs. Smith]]'' relationship."<ref name="f" /> During a blizzard, Brad shows up at the Abbott Cabin where Sharon is staying, and professes his love for her. After she rejects him, Brad saves her son Noah from drowning in an icy lake, but fell in the ice himself and dies a hero.<ref name="Reu" /> Case said a guilty Sharon "wasn't nice to him leading up to that day", describing her losing Brad as "awful" and a "tragic loss".<ref name="f" />

{{quote box
|width = 17em
|border = 1px
|align=right
|bgcolor= LightCyan 
|fontsize = 88%
|quote = "I didn<U+2019>t understand how I was going to sell a love story between Sharon and Victor for obvious reasons. What motivated Sharon to fall in love with Victor when she<U+2019>s in love with Adam and Nick?"<ref name=SOU/>
|salign = right
|source =<U+2014>Case, on Sharon's romance with Victor (2012)
}}

Unlike Nick's mother [[Nikki Newman]] ([[Melody Thomas Scott]]), his father [[Victor Newman]] ([[Eric Braeden]]) adored Sharon, who he maintained a "father-daughter" relationship with over the years.<ref>{{cite news|title=TV Soap Updates: Here's what you missed|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=Q3RTAAAAIBAJ&sjid=JIYDAAAAIBAJ&pg=2462,1751505&dq=sharon+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|accessdate=December 22, 2011|newspaper=[[Daily News (Kingsport)|Daily News]]|location=Kingsport|date= February 14, 1996}}</ref><ref name=FF>{{cite web|title=Nick vs. Victor: Now and Then|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/nick-vs-victor-now-and-then-0|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=([[Source Interlink]])|accessdate=January 27, 2012|author=Soap Opera Digest|date=January 9, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Ann|first=Mary|title=Speaking Of Soaps|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=KLpJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=lBANAAAAIBAJ&pg=3950,3675515&dq=nick+and+sharon+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|accessdate=December 24, 2011|newspaper=The Madison Courier|date=February 7, 2003}}</ref> Case described Victor as Sharon's hero, who gave her a "security blanket feeling". She said he was Sharon's "father figure, but not quite." "When she was younger she saw him as that, and then when she grew up she saw him less as a father and more like a hero".<ref name="soaps interview">{{cite web|last=Soaps.com|title=Soaps.com In Depth With Y&R's Sharon Case! Part II|url=http://soaps.sheknows.com/youngandrestless/news/id/3433/Soapscom_In_Depth_With_YandRs_Sharon_Case_Part_II/|work=She Knows Soaps|publisher=soaps.sheknows.com|accessdate=January 21, 2012|date=February 3, 2009}}</ref> However, in January 2012, the dynamics between the characters changed when Victor non-romantically marries Sharon to protect his assets while in jail; the marriage is annulled days later.<ref>{{cite web|title=On Sale Now <U+2013> CBS Soaps In Depth "Victor Proposes to Sharon!"|url=http://cbs.soapsindepth.com/on-sale-now/|work=[[Bauer Media Group]]|accessdate=January 6, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Montanari|first=Mary|title='The Young and the Restless': Highlights, Sneak Peek and Spoilers 1-16-17|url=http://entertainment.gather.com/viewArticle.action?articleId=281474981030409|publisher=entertainment.gather.com|date=January 17, 2012|accessdate=January 27, 2012}}</ref> Months later, they develop a real romance. Morrow told ''Soaps In Depth'' that he was "puzzled" as to why Nick wasn't showing "legitimate anger" over the relationship,<ref name="Joshy">{{cite web|last=Giddens|first=Jamey|title=Young and Restless' Joshua Morrow on 'Shictor': 'I Was Always Kind of Surprised That Nick Just Accepted This From His Dad'|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/08/23/young-and-restless-joshua-morrow-on-shictor-i-was-always-kind-of-surprised-that-nick-just|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=September 1, 2012|date=August 23, 2012}}</ref> while Braeden also wasn't happy with the storyline, stating: "We all have gone through periods of playing something we didn't really like to play so much, but you do it. Sharon is a wonderful actress".<ref name="MSN"/> 

In August 2012, Victor and Sharon re-marry, but he disappears shortly after.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bowe|first=Jillian|title=Where in The World is Victor Newman on The Young and the Restless?|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/08/03/the-young-and-the-restless-spoilers-tucker-and-sharon-team-up|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=August 23, 2012|date=August 3, 2012}}</ref> Sharon then burns up their prenuptial agreement and takes over his company; Case felt that the writers could have handled the storyline "a million other ways" without having Sharon marry Victor.<ref name="MSN"/> The actress labeled the relationship as [[incest]]uous, stating: "Sometimes controversial storylines can work because you're bringing attention to a controversial issue that the nation is trying to decide on. But this was not one of those things. Everybody is universally against incest! It was just so upsetting to the audience."<ref name="Crazy Talk">{{cite book|last=McElwain |first=Julie |chapter=Crazy Talk |title=CBS Soaps In Depth |date=October 22, 2012 |pages=55<U+2013>57}}</ref> The marriage, which ended following Victor's return, was considered an "inside joke" for the actors.<ref name="Inside">{{cite web|last=Schaefer|first=Glen|title=Y&R star says show on <U+2018>cusp of change<U+2019> after writers axed|url=http://www.theprovince.com/star+says+show+cusp+change+after+writers+axed/7393387/story.html#ixzz29ZAoXuVV|work=[[The Province]]|publisher=[[Postmedia]]|accessdate=October 26, 2012|date=October 15, 2012}}</ref>

===Relationship with Adam Newman===
[[File:Michael Muhney 2010 Daytime Emmy Awards.jpg|160px|left|thumb|[[Michael Muhney]] portrays Sharon's "darker" love interest, Adam.]]
[[Adam Newman]] ([[Michael Muhney]]) kidnaps Sharon's newborn baby Faith and gives her to [[Ashley Abbott]] ([[Eileen Davidson]]) to avoid being caught in a scheme. Previously, Adam caused Ashley to have a miscarriage and a [[hysterical pregnancy]], allowing her to believe she was pregnant. Despite this, Adam bonds with Sharon out of grief; however, they fall in love and marry. Muhney told [[SoapNet]] that Adam "Unequivocally" loves her 100% explained that "You can argue as much logic as you want about what Adam has done and what he is doing."<ref>{{cite web|title=SOAPnet Interviews "Evil Adam"|url=http://sn.soapnet.go.com/news/article/soapnet-interviews-evil-adam?page=0,1|work=[[SoapNet]]|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]|accessdate=October 26, 2012|date=January 2010}}</ref> Adam kidnapping Faith is revealed, but Sharon remains in love with him, upsetting the town and her close friends.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bowe|first=Jillian|title=The Young and The Restless Spoilers: Genoa City vs. Sharon!|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2010/12/06/the-young-and-the-restless-spoilers-genoa-city-vs-sharon|work=[[Zap2It]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=November 7, 2012|date=December 6, 2010}}</ref><ref name="i" />  Case described Sharon's ability to forgive Adam as a "tough pill to swallow".<ref>{{cite web|title='Young and the Restless' Q&A with Sharon Case|url=http://www.nola.com/tv/index.ssf/2010/11/young_and_the_restless_qa_with_1.html|publisher=[[Advance Publications]]|accessdate=December 24, 2011}}</ref> Jamey Giddens of Zap2It described them as "inappropriate" yet "red-hot".<ref name="RHH" /> After trying to help Adam get acquitted for his ex-wife Skye's murder, she ends up in jail herself.<ref name=d>{{cite web|title=(Young and Restless Recaps) Y&R Week of April 11, 2011|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/yr-week-april-11-2011|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=[[American Media, Inc.]]|accessdate=December 24, 2011}}</ref> Despite this, Case still supported 'Shadam' noting that the pairing "took us all by surprise" and she said that: "that is what I was referring to with this storyline because of the pace and the vitality that "Shadam" has".<ref name="e">{{cite web|url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/news/yrs-sharon-case-interview-shadam-sham-shick-more/2011/07/05/ |title=Y&R<U+2019>s Sharon Case Interview: 'Shadam', 'Sham', 'Shick' & more!|publisher=Michael Fairman |work=On-Air On-Soaps |date=June 5, 2011 |accessdate=November 23, 2011}}</ref> While on the run, Adam believes she is dead, and Sharon sleeps with [[Sam Gibson (The Young and the Restless)|Sam Gibson]] ([[Sean Patrick Flannery]]). Adam feels betrayed when Sharon returns to Genoa City, and cons her into a jailhouse wedding where he dumps her, leaving her heartbroken and angry.<ref>{{cite web|last=Badgett|first=Becca|title=Sharon's Jailhouse Wedding a Shambles on 'The Young and the Restless'|url=http://tv.yahoo.com/news/sharons-jailhouse-wedding-shambles-young-restless-171000891.html|work=[[Yahoo!]] |publisher=[[Yahoo! Inc]]|accessdate=December 24, 2011|date=August 2, 2011}}</ref> 

In order to spend time with Faith, Nick forces Sharon to get a restraining order against Adam. The night before the order becomes active, Adam and Sharon have sex.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Y&R Sharon and Adam have Sex!|journal=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=[[American Media, Inc.]]|date=December 27, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Week of January 2, 2012|url=http://soapcentral.com/yr/scoop.php|accessdate=January 5, 2012}}</ref> Jae' Jones of [[Yahoo!]] noted that Sharon's actions would "always" lead her back to Adam.<ref name="Yahoo" /> After Adam is attacked and loses his vision, Sharon takes him back to his mother's farm in [[Kansas]] where they get back together. They are engaged, but soon after returning to Genoa City she leaves Adam when more of his past crimes came to light.<ref name="Feb1">{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless March 2012|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/episode-info/monthly/?month=2&year=2012|publisher=[[Sony Entertainment Television]]|accessdate=October 30, 2012}}</ref><ref name=541d>{{cite web|author=The Young and the Restless |url=http://www.cbs.com/shows/the_young_and_the_restless/episodes/100614 |title=The Young and the Restless: Monday, March 5, 2012 <U+2013> on |publisher=[[CBS]] |date=March 5, 2012 |accessdate=March 13, 2012}}</ref><ref name=541d /><ref>{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless Sneak Peek: Week of 3/5/12|url=http://sn.soapnet.go.com/news/article/the-young-and-the-restless-sneak-peek-week-of-3512|work=[[SoapNet]]|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]|accessdate=March 10, 2012}}</ref> 

Despite marrying [[Chelsea Lawson]] ([[Melissa Claire Egan]]), Adam helps Sharon through an emotional breakdown that led her to burn down Victor's home, and covers her tracks so that she isn't arrested. Chelsea is enraged when Adam hides Sharon out in a small cottage on on their property and becomes insecure about her marriage;<ref>{{cite journal|title=Y&R Explodes!|journal=[[Soaps In Depth]]|date=November 19, 2012|accessdate=November 22, 2012}}</ref> Luke Kerr of Zap2it opined that Chelsea is "out of her league" against Sharon.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kerr|first=Luke|title=Sharon and Chelsea go Toe-to-Toe Over Adam on The Young and the Restless!|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/11/26/sharon-and-chelsea-go-toe-to-toe-over-adam-on-the-young-and-the-restless|work=[[Zap2It]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=December 2, 2012|date=November 26, 2012}}</ref> Adam and Sharon later share a kiss, witnessed by Chelsea.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Episode 10049|url=|series=The Young and the Restless|serieslink=The Young and the Restless|credits=Series Producer: [[Jill Farren Phelps]]; Writer: [[Josh Griffith]] |network=[[CBS]]|station=|airdate=December 7, 2012|seriesno=40}}</ref> While Case feels that Nick and Sharon's history "held more weight", she said Sharon's relationship with Adam is "just as deep".<ref name="Crazy Talk">{{cite book|last=McElwain |first=Julie |chapter=Crazy Talk |title=CBS Soaps In Depth |date=October 22, 2012 |pages=55<U+2013>57}}</ref>

===Fugitivity and alter ego===
On January 24, 2011, Sharon is arrested for the murder of Adam's ex-wife Skye Newman (Laura Stone).<ref>{{cite web|title=Young and Restless Recaps <U+2013> Week of January 24, 2011|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/yr-week-january-24-2011|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=[[American Media, Inc.]]|accessdate=January 16, 2012}}</ref> Sharon had previously gone to [[Hawaii]] to find Skye, which she did, but Skye ended up falling into an active volcano. ''[[CBS Soaps In Depth]]'' reported that an unhappy Sharon may commit suicide.<ref name=suicide>{{cite web|last=Giddens|first=Jamey|title=The Perils of Sharon Continue on Young and Restless|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2011/04/08/the-perils-of-sharon-on-young-and-restless|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=July 27, 2012|date=April 8, 2011}}</ref> After being sentenced to prison for life, Sharon claims she is ill and retreats to a bathroom where Adam hid a duffel bag for her escape. She smothers an officer with [[chloroform]] and escapes through a window. Adam gives her a fake ID, passports and cash. She stopped at a gas station, where she dyes her hair brunette and changes into a "skimpy" outfit.<ref name="SheriC" /> Case said that although it was fun for the storyline, she didn't like being a brunette.<ref name="MSN2">{{cite web|last=Barnert|first=Deanna|title=Sharon Case Q&A: Take a July 4th Road Trip Into Sharon's Past on 'The Young and the Restless'|url=http://social.entertainment.msn.com/tv/blogs/tv-buzz-blogpost.aspx?post=866cfb6f-4856-4e6a-880e-d7e4eaa23731|publisher=[[MSN]], [[Microsoft]]|accessdate=November 26, 2012|date=July 1, 2011}}</ref> Later, Sharon is carjacked and has all of her possessions stolen; the female carjacker dies after her car crashes. The body is identified as Sharon's, leaving her family and friends believing she died.<ref name="SheriC">{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless April 2011|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/episode-info/monthly/?month=7&year=2011|publisher=[[Sony Entertainment Television]]|accessdate=October 25, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.freezepage.com/1351221755JAOLQEXVLP|archivedate=October 15, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Hughes|first=Adam|title=Sharon Newman Returns to Genoa City on 'The Young and the Restless'|url=http://tv.yahoo.com/news/sharon-newman-returns-genoa-city-young-restless-160900861.html|work=[[Yahoo!]]|accessdate=October 25, 2012|date=July 12, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Young and Restless Recaps <U+2013> Week of April 18, 2011|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/yr-week-april-18-2011|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=([[Source Interlink]])|accessdate=January 16, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Young and Restless Recaps <U+2014> Y&R Week of April 18, 2011|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/yr-week-april-18-2011|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=[[American Media, Inc.]]|accessdate=December 28, 2011}}</ref> Case, who always wanted to do a ''Mr & Mrs. Smith''-type storyline, claimed that when Sharon became a fugitive, she had her chance.<ref name="f" /> The actress enjoyed playing the "more aggressive" side of Sharon when she attacked the prison guard.<ref name="ze" /> Sharon then poses under the [[pseudonym]] Sheri Coleman for months in [[New Mexico]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Young and Restless Recaps <U+2013> Week of May 9, 2011|url=http://www.soapoperadigest.com/content/yr-week-may-9-2011|work=[[Soap Opera Digest]]|publisher=([[Source Interlink]])|accessdate= January 16, 2012}}</ref> While in New Mexico, she romances a man named [[Sam Gibson (The Young and the Restless)|Sam Gibson]] ([[Sean Patrick Flannery]]), who let her stay at his farm. She also bonda with a young local girl named Piper, and the animals at the barn.<ref name="SheriC"/> Case said that although she hoped the "recklessness" of the storyline would continue, she found Sharon's storyline with Sam, Piper and the animals "really beautiful".<ref name="ze">{{cite web|last=Bedigian|first=Laurie|title=Michigan<U+2019>s Sharon Case talks about life in Genoa City|work=[[examiner]]|publisher=[[Philip Anschutz]]|date=July 5, 2011}}</ref> Case had hoped the story would take a different root where she could meet up with Adam on the run, creating a "[[Bonnie and Clyde]]" scenario.<ref name="ze" /> 

Head writer [[Maria Arena Bell]] dedicated the [[4th of July]] episode to Sharon, reminding viewers of "what the character has been through".<ref name="j">{{cite web|title=A Special Sharon Episode|url=http://cbs.soapsindepth.com/2011/06/a-special-sharon-episode.html|work=CBS Soaps In Depth |accessdate=December 28, 2011}}</ref> Bell stated that the episode "shed more light on Sharon and all the factors that caused her to be in this situation, why she's acted the way she has and why she's gone into the pit of [low] self-esteem." Case commented that she wants to show why Sharon is in "the place that she's in" during the episode, which would examine her life over the years.<ref name="j" /> Jae' Jones from [[Yahoo!]] analysed the storyline in anticipation of Sharon's homecoming, hoping that Nick, Adam and Noah shouldn't forgive her because of all the "unforgivable things" she has done, especially her "devious" move of letting them believe she was dead. Jones said that some viewers "will say she did what she thought she had to do" even though it seemed as if it were easy; but "it's never that easy to walk away from the people you love".<ref name="Yahoo">{{cite web|last=Jones|first=Jae'|title=Will Nick and Adam Forgive Sharon on 'The Young and the Restless'?|url=http://tv.yahoo.com/news/nick-adam-forgive-sharon-young-restless-201400976.html|work=[[Yahoo!]] |publisher=[[Yahoo! Inc.]]|accessdate=January 10, 2012|coauthors=Jae' Jones|date=July 30, 2011}}</ref> In July, Sharon is found and arrested in New Mexico, returning  to Genoa City where she was sentenced to life in prison again. Case said that she was happy to be at the barn because it was "relaxing", but became "restless" and wanted to leave, and was glad the character was finally coming home.<ref name="MSN" /> Nick is furious with Sharon, and Adam dumps her for sleeping with Sam.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless July 2011|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/episode-info/monthly/?month=7&year=2011|publisher=[[Sony Pictures Television]]|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref> Almost a year after the initial accident at the volcano, evidence is provided in November 2011 proving Sharon didn't murder Skye, acquitting her finally of the crime she didn't commit.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless November 2011|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/episode-info/monthly/?month=11&year=2011|publisher=[[Sony Pictures Television]]|accessdate=October 25, 2012}}</ref>

=== Mental health ===
In 2009, Sharon suffers from [[kleptomania]], an impulse control disorder that causes people to steal, causing her to steal items from people and stores. Eventually, she is forced to admit herself into a [[psychiatric hospital]] while pregnant.<ref name="SCC">{{cite web|title=About Y&R: Who's Who In Genoa City {{!}} Sharon Newman |url=http://soapcentral.com/yr/whoswho/sharon.php? |publisher=Soap Central (soapcentral.com)|accessdate=July 27, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Garrett|first=Tommy|title=Leading Ladies, Look Of Deception|url=http://www.canyon-news.com/artman2/publish/Television/Leading_Ladies_Look_Of_Deception_printer.php|accessdate=July 27, 2012|newspaper=[[Canyon News]]|publisher=Glen Kelly|date=April 7, 2010}}</ref> Case told ''[[TV Guide]]'' that all of the character's "craziness" makes sense, and she welcomes the challenge because she decides how "functional Sharon appears to people" and gets into debates with directors.<ref>{{cite web|last=Richenthal|first=Matt|title=Sharon Case Welcomes Challenge on The Young and the Restless|url=http://www.tvfanatic.com/2009/05/sharon-case-welcomes-challenge-on-the-young-and-the-restless/|publisher=TV Fanatic|accessdate=December 22, 2011}}</ref> Michael Fairman noted that Sharon is "acting so bizzare".<ref name="f">{{cite web|url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/the-young-and-the-restless/the-sharon-case-interview-the-young-and-the-restless/2009/02/25/ |title=The Sharon Case Interview |publisher=Michaelfairmansoaps.com |date=February 25, 2009 |accessdate=November 18, 2010}}</ref> Case said her breakdown was due in part to Brad Carlton's death along with her marriage to Jack breaking down, considering every time Sharon "mapped it out", her life is "torn to pieces".<ref name="f" /> Sharon has since experienced kleptomania on and off.<ref name="SCC" /><ref>{{cite web|last=Bowe|first=Jillian|title=The Young and the Restless Spoilers: The Bug Busts Phyllis!|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/07/09/the-young-and-the-restless-spoilers-the-bug-busts-phyllis|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=July 27, 2012|date=July 9, 2012}}</ref> 

In 2012, after Victor disappears following his wedding to Sharon, she realizes that she needs to be married to Victor for more than eight days to walk away with his money. She then burns their [[prenuptial agreement]] after Nikki sends her a text from Victor's phone, saying he dumped her.<ref name="TEXT">{{cite web|last=Bowe|first=Jillian|title=SPOILERS: Can Nick and Victoria Squash a Power Hungry Sharon on The Young and the Restless?|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/08/09/can-nick-and-victoria-squash-sharons-power-hungry-quest-on-the-young-and-the-restless|work=[[Zap2It]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=August 23, 2012|date=August 9, 2012}}</ref> Sharon decides to take over his company, Newman Enterprises, in his absence.<ref name="TakeOver">{{cite web|last=Giddens|first=Jimmy|title=Young and Restless' Sharon: 'I'm Kinda Starting to Like Being The New Mrs. Victor Newman'|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/08/13/young-and-restless-sharon-im-kinda-starting-to-like-being-the-new-mrs-victor-newman|work=[[Zap2It]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=August 23, 2012|date=August 13, 2012}}</ref> Case thought a scene where Sharon crashed a Newman board meeting was "fun" and "different", confessing that she wanted to play "this version of Sharon" for years.<ref name="FunnyBest"/> As Victor's proxy, she became CEO of the company, secretly aided by manipulative businessman [[Tucker McCall]] ([[Stephen Nichols]]).<ref name="CEO">{{cite web|last=Bowe|first=Jillian|title=Sharon is Voted in as SPOILER on The Young and the Restless|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/08/16/spoiler-sharon-voted-ceo-of-newman-enterprises-on-the-young-and-the-restless|work=[[Zap2It]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=August 23, 2012|date=August 16, 2012}}</ref> Stock prices for Newman fell, with Tucker secretly buying them. Case hoped the writers wouldn't go the "typical" way where the storyline ends with Victor wreaking "havoc on everyone".<ref name="MSN">{{cite web|last=Barnet|first=Deanna|title=He Said, She Said: Eric Braeden and Sharon Case|url=http://social.entertainment.msn.com/tv/blogs/tv-buzz-blogpost.aspx?post=0a6b5db5-ae92-486c-b49b-3004810aa304#scpshrtu|publisher=[[MSN]], [[Microsoft]]|accessdate=August 24, 2012|date=August 24, 2012}}</ref><ref name="NewmanHealth"/> Sharon was labeled the "Newman's Grim Reaper" by the media,<ref>{{cite web|last=Kerr|first=Luke|title=SOAP BYTES: Is Sharon the Grim Reaper on Young and Restless? Are Liam and Hope Really over on Bold and Beautiful?|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/08/30/soap-bytes-is-sharon-the-grim-reaper-on-the-young-and-the-restless-are-liam-and-hope-real|work=[[Zap2It]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=September 5, 2012|date=August 30, 2012}}</ref> leaving Nick and Victoria desperate to rescue the company from her clutches. They prove her history of kleptomania and have her go back to the psychiatric ward for an evaluation, which she passes, and soon returns to her position of CEO.<ref name="NewmanHealth"/> Case called Sharon's return a "fun aspect of the story".<ref name="MSN" /> Sharon continued behave out of character. She discovers that Victor is in fact alive, but instead tells everyone he died after being asked to identify a burnt body which wasn't his. Case said Sharon was taking advantage of the situation.<ref name="MSN" /> At Victor's funeral, Sharon wore white and nearly married Tucker afterwards. Victor then returns and throws Sharon out of his family, home and company.<ref name="NewmanHealth"/> Eventually, despite her crimes, Sharon is able to get away with no jail time.<ref name="NewmanHealth">{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless April 2011|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/episode-info/monthly/?month=9&year=2012|publisher=[[Sony Entertainment Television]]|accessdate=October 26, 2012|archiveurl=http://www.freezepage.com/1351223587YRFLTJTWSL|archivedate=October 26, 2012}}</ref> At this point, Aaron Hagey-MacKay of [[GlobalTV]] said Sharon was "crazy".<ref>{{cite web|last=Hagey-MacKay|first=Aaron|title=Genoa City Update: Has Sharon Lost Her Marbles?|url=http://www.globaltv.com/soapbubble/2012/September/Genoa_City_Update__has_Sharon_lost_her_Marbles_/|publisher=[[Global TV]]|accessdate=October 26, 2012|date=September 2012}}</ref> 

{{quote box
|width = 18em
|border = 1px
|align=right
