Case revealed that she wasn't worried about the storyline, because the writers had a plan to explain Sharon's behavior.<ref name="FunnyBest" /> Newly appointed head writer [[Josh Griffith]] told ''TV Guide'' that the character would reach a final "total mental breakdown" which will take her to "the edge and over it" before being rebuilt.<ref name=rebuild/> Griffith said the breakdown will help her find salvation, with a "stronger, more together, more evolved Sharon" emerging at the end of it.<ref name=rebuild/> Sharon ends up having a breakdown at the main-house of the Newman ranch, and while under the influence of alcohol, burns down the house.<ref>{{cite web|title=Proceeding As Planned. - The Young and the Restless Daily Updates - Soaps.com|url=http://soaps.sheknows.com/youngandrestless/update/id/16469/Proceeding_As_Planned/|accessdate=October 25, 2012|date=October 18, 2012}}</ref> Griffith stated that the damage Sharon has done to the Newman family is "physical, professional and emotional."<ref name=rebuild/> After seeing a doctor, Sharon is diagnosed with [[bipolar disorder]] and begins treatment for it. She is alarmed after finding out that she has to take prescribed medication, possibly for the rest of her life.<ref name="Eppie">{{Cite episode
 | title =The Young and the Restless #10034 | accessdate =November 14, 2012 | network =[[CBS]] | date =November 14, 2012 | season =40 | minutes =35:09 | quote =It's a very common treatment for [[bipolar disorder]] | language =English 
}}</ref> Case was happy with the outcome of the storyline, as were viewers of the show.<ref name="HwP" /> In January 2013, she told ''Soap Opera Uncensored'': "When Sharon battled her emotional problems, that also took a lot of work but in a different way.  Playing someone who is bipolar is very exhausting but it worked out perfectly and explained all of Sharon<U+2019>s past behavior. I applaud Josh for making that decision because I think it makes the most sense considering her history."<ref name="HwP">{{cite web|last=Fairman|first=Michael|title=Y&R<U+2019>s Sharon Case Chats On Sharon Newman<U+2019>s Bipolar Disorder & New Love Interest!|url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/news/yrs-sharon-case-chats-on-sharon-newmans-bipolar-disorder-new-love-interest/2013/01/12/|work=On-Air On-Soaps|publisher=Michael Fairman Soaps, Inc.|accessdate=January 15, 2013|date=January 12, 2013}}</ref>

==Storylines==
===Backstory ===
Born in September 1975, Sharon Collins grew up in [[Madison, Wisconsin]]. She lived with her mother [[List of The Young and the Restless characters (1990s)#Doris Collins|Doris Collins]] ([[Karen Hensel]]), who was confined to a wheelchair as a result of chasing a rebellious Sharon years earlier. Sharon became pregnant by her high-school boyfriend [[List of The Young and the Restless characters (2000s)#Frank Barritt|Frank Barritt]] (Phil Dozois), but gave the child up for adoption.<ref name="Character Bio - Sharon Abbott"/> 

===1994<U+2013>===
In 1994, 18-year old Sharon arrives in Genoa City and begins attending a local high-school. She meets Nick Newman, the son of rich business tycoon Victor Newman, who is dating [[List of The Young and the Restless characters (1990s)#Amy Wilson|Amy Wilson]] ([[Julianne Morris]]). However, Nick falls in love with Sharon and they become a couple, amid Sharon's ex-boyfriend [[Matt Clark (The Young and the Restless)|Matt Clark]]'s ([[Eddie Cibrian]]) attempts to win her back. They briefly part ways after Matt exposes Sharon's secret about having a baby when she was sixteen, but reunite shortly after. Later, an angry Matt rapes Sharon in his car, traumatizing her.<ref name="MSN2" /> Nick and Sharon are engaged, and she soon tells him about the rape, which leads him to set out for revenge on Matt. Matt is shot, and Nick was the main suspect. Following a lengthy trial, Nick is sent to jail, though was acquitted several months later when Amy came forward as the shooter. After Matt fled town, Nick and Sharon marry, although Sharon soon becomes insecure and stops taking [[birth control]] which  results in a pregnancy. Once Nick clarifies that he wasn't ready to become a father, Sharon nearly has an abortion, but Nick stops her. In 1997, she gives birth to Noah Newman, who nearly dies after being born prematurely. While he was critically ill, Sharon's best friend Grace Turner tracks down the child she gave birth to as a teenager, Cassie, and brings her to Genoa City, believing it was lessen the pain if Noah died. However, Noah survives, and Grace decides to raise Cassie as her own. Her plans are soon foiled, with Nick and Sharon taking over custody of Cassie. Prior, Nick cheated on Sharon with Grace which nearly ended their marriage, but Cassie's custody battle reunited them. 

In 2001, Matt ([[Rick Hearst]]) returns to town after plastic surgery with a fake identity, Carter Mills. He attempts to rape Sharon and succeeds; his identity is ultimately revealed and he dies after driving off a cliff. Sharon ends up pregnant, with Matt possibly fathering her child. During an argument with Nick, Sharon trips and falls, giving birth to a stillborn baby girl. After a paternity test, Nick is revealed to be the baby's father. Sharon finds solace in the Newman ranch's handyman [[Diego Guittierez]] ([[Greg Vaughan]]) who had been dating Nick's sister Victoria at the time. Her unfaithfulness resulted in her splitting up with Nick. Nick later sees Sharon kissing Victor, which leaves Sharon humiliated and depressed. She leaves town, and while away, meets Cameron Kirsten, a man who has an affair with her and later abuses her brutally. Sharon returns to Genoa after her wounds healed, but is horrified when Cameron comes to town for business with Newman Enterprises. Sharon briefly believes that she killed him during an encounter, but he shows up alive and is later tracked down and jailed for his crimes. Sharon becomes restless in her housewife role and desires to become a stripper. Nick gives her a spokeswomen job at [[Jabot Cosmetics]] to keep her busy. In 2005, Cassie dies in a car accident after driving underage. During Sharon's time of grief, Nick cheats on her with Phyllis Summers. Sharon herself has a [[one night stand]] with Victoria's husband, Brad Carlton. Nick and Sharon divorce after eleven years after Phyllis ends up pregnant with Nick's baby.

Sharon romances Phyllis' ex, Jack Abbott, and they eventually marry. Phyllis discovers the truth about her affair with Brad and blackmails her. During a cliff-side photo-shoot, Phyllis threatens to tell Jack about the affair, resulting in an altercation. Sharon and her best friend [[Drucilla Winters]] ([[Victoria Rowell]]) fall from the cliff, which resulted in Drucilla's death. Sharon is found dead, but is successfully revived. Later, Nick is presumed dead after his plane crashes, but returns alive with amnesia. He believes he is still married to Sharon, but regains his memory and returns to Phyllis. Jack, Phyllis, Nick and Sharon develop a magazine together entitled ''Restless Style''; but clashes between the quad drive Jack and Sharon out of the company. In October 2008, Sharon and Nick run into each other in [[Paris, France]]. They end up kissing on the bridge, which Phyllis witnesses. Sharon divorces Jack due to his constant lies, and makes love to Nick at the Abbott cabin where the two profess their love for one another. Confused, Sharon spirals out of control and experiences [[kleptomania]]. She has a brief affair with Jack's brother, [[Billy Abbott]] ([[Billy Miller (actor)|Billy Miller]]). Sharon ends up pregnant, and Nick jumps back and forth between her and Phyllis. He ultimately remains with Phyllis when Sharon lies by stating Jack is the father of the child. Sharon checks herself into a psychiatric hospital after her kleptomania got out of control. She gives birth to a baby girl named Faith, who is stolen by Adam Newman, Nick's brother, and presents it to Jack's sister [[Ashley Abbott]] ([[Eileen Davidson]]), who he caused to miscarry her own child. Believing her baby is dead, Sharon becomes close with Adam, who bonds with her out of guilt. Sharon and Adam are married, though the truth about Faith is soon revealed and the marriage ends. Months later, Sharon shoots Adam while he tries to visit her at the Abbott cabin, believing he was trying to break in; he survives. Nick and Sharon reunite briefly, but split up once again after she cheats on him with Adam, who follows her to [[New Orleans]] where they slept together.

Adam is convicted for the murder of his ex-wife, [[List of The Young and the Restless characters (2000s)#Skye Lockhart|Skye Newman]] (Laura Stone). Sharon devotes herself to helping him but ends up finding herself arrested for murder after finding Skye in Hawaii, where Skye fell into a volcano. After escaping and returning after months of people believing she was dead, Sharon was acquitted and then dedicates herself to Victor, who is in jail while protecting Nikki from a murder sentence. Victor briefly marries Sharon, non-romantically, to protect his assets, although they had the marriage annulled two weeks later. Adam is believed to be permanently blind and Sharon sympathetically helps him recover from an attack. They reunite, but more of his past schemes are revealed. After suffering from another nervous breakdown and bipolar disorder which caused her to marry Victor again and take over Newman Enterprises, Sharon gets her life back and is re-hired at Newman as vice president of R&D in 2013.

==Reception==
{{Quote box|width=20%|align=right|bgcolor=LightCyan|quote="Flawless; that<U+2019>s the word used to describe the acting ability of Sharon Case, who portrays long-suffering Sharon Newman [...] thankfully we have the beautiful Sharon Case playing the role of a lifetime and giving the performance of a lifetime"<ref>{{cite web|last=Garret|first=Tommy|title=Shocking Performance By <U+2018>Y&R<U+2019> Actress Sharon Case Leads To Gold|url=http://www.highlighthollywood.com/2011/12/31/shocking-performance-by-yr-actress-sharon-case-leads-to-gold/|work=Hollywood Highlight|publisher=highlighthollywood.com|accessdate=November 13, 2012|date=November 31, 2011}}</ref>|source=<U+2014>Tommy Garret of ''Highlight Hollywood'' on Case's performance (2012)}}
===General===
Despite crimes and faults, [[Global Regina]] describes Sharon as a central heroine, who has endured many challenges to get to where she is today.<ref name="heroine">{{cite web|title=Global Regina {{!}} Sharon Case|url=http://www.globalregina.com/Sharon+Case/3310689/story.html|publisher=[[Global Regina]]|accessdate=December 22, 2011}}</ref> In 1995, Case compared Sharon to a younger version of [[Jill Foster Abbott]] ([[Jess Walton]]), telling ''[[Soap Opera Weekly]]'' that Jill "was kind of like Sharon. She was nice ... no one thought she was a gold digger<U+2014>at first."<ref name="SharonJill"/> Kathleen Sloan, a writer from ''[[Toronto Star]]'', in turn stated that Nick's mother, who felt Sharon was a gold-digger, may be right after all. Sloan noted that Sharon's "angelic demeanor" might mask "a devil in disguise".<ref name="SharonJill">{{cite news|last=Sloan|first=Kathleen|title=Restless Sharon may turn devilish|url=http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/21226542.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Aug+13%2C+1995&author=&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=Restless+Sharon+may+turn+devilish+Kathleen+Sloan&pqatl=google|accessdate=October 26, 2012|newspaper=[[Toronto Star]]|date=August 13, 1995}}</ref> In 2009, Luke Kerr of [[Zap2it]] noted that all of Sharon's love interests<U+2014>including Jack, Brad and Nicholas<U+2014>all "seem to think" that she is "the perfect woman".<ref>{{cite web|last=Kerr|first=Luke|title=Is Sharon Collins Newman Abbott The Perfect Woman?|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2009/01/sharon-collins-newman-abbott-the-perfect-woman|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=July 12, 2012|date=January 29, 2009}}</ref> Jamey Giddens, another writer from Zap2It, described her as soap opera's "hottest mess".<ref name=suicide/> 

During [[Maria Arena Bell]]'s time as the show's executive producer and head writer, the character's storyline descended into an unfavorable creative direction. Bell had made an oath to make the character a "stronger woman". Jillian Bowe of Zap2It heavily criticized Bell for not living up to this pledge. Bowe wrote: "Has transforming Sharon into a promiscuous, recovering kleptomanic, who never considers what her sexual choices will mean for her children, really made her stronger in [Bell]'s eyes?" Additionally, she stated that Sharon's "beloved" character is being "utterly assassinated, via one ill-conceived storyline and/or romance after another".
<ref name="MABCritic">{{cite web|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/06/19/deconstructing-the-young-and-the-restless-sharon |title=How The Complete and Utter Destruction of Sharon Newman Parallels MAB's Dismantling of The Young and the Restless &#124; Daytime Confidential |publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]] |date= |accessdate=November 7, 2012}}</ref> Michael Logan from ''[[TV Guide]]'' commented that the character turned from "heroine" to a "pyscho slut-nut" when she's "not channeling [[Joan Crawford]] in the Pepsi board room."<ref name=rebuild>{{cite web|last=Logan|first=Michael|title=Exclusive: New Young and the Restless Head Writer Josh Griffith Talks About the Future|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Young-Restless-Writer-1053629.aspx|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=September 26, 2012|date=September 24, 2012}}</ref> Another writer from Zap2It praised Case has giving "one wonky storyline after another" her best efforts, in a character that was "once beloved" but has been "royally assassinated".<ref name="ra">{{cite web|title=Daytime Confidential Top 20, July 2012|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/08/15/daytime-confidential-top-20-july-2012?page=0,9|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=August 24, 2012|date=August 15, 2012}}</ref> A September 2012 scene where Sharon wore white to her husband Victor's funeral was described by Joshua Morrow as "one of the best and funniest scenes" ever shot in the show's history.<ref name="FunnyBest">{{cite web|last=Fairman|first=Michael|title=The Sharon Case Interview <U+2013> The Young and the Restless|url=http://michaelfairmansoaps.com/the-young-and-the-restless/the-sharon-case-interview-the-young-and-the-restless-2/2012/10/03/|work=On-Air On-Soaps|publisher=Michael Fairman|accessdate=October 29, 2012|date=October 3, 2012}}</ref> Tommy Garrett of ''[[Canyon News]]'' wrote that: "Maria Bell knows that consummate actress Sharon Case plays the consummate heroine Sharon Newman with aplomb."<ref>{{cite news|last=Garrett|first=Tommy|title=Leading Ladies, In The Name Of Love|url=http://www.canyon-news.com/artman2/publish/Television/Leading_Ladies_In_The_Name_Of_Love.php|accessdate=July 27, 2012|newspaper=[[Canyon News]]|date=December 30, 2010}}</ref>

=== Romances ===
Sharon's relationship with Nick has been met with popularity from viewers; they are considered a prominent [[supercouple]] in the realm of soap operas.<ref name="supercouple list" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Supercouple Case and Morrow React to Diamont's Exit|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2008/12/young-and-restless-supercouple-case-and-morrow-react-to-diamonts-exit|work=[[Zap2It]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=January 28, 2012|author=Jamey Giddens|date=December 13, 2008}}</ref> The pairing are referred to by the [[portmanteau]] of 'Shick' in [[social media]].<ref name="e" /> Kim Potts of ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' placed Nick and Sharon 16th on a list of "Greatest Soap Opera Supercouples".<ref name="supercouple list">{{cite web|title=Greatest Soap Opera Supercouples|url=http://www.aoltv.ca/2010/01/21/greatest-soap-opera-supercouples/|publisher=Hufflepost TV (aoltv.ca)|accessdate=January 27, 2012|author=Kim Potts|date=January 21, 2010}}</ref> Potts said that the couple's "young love" hasn't turned out to be "enduring love", but a reunion is "always a possibility".<ref name="supercouple list" /> SoapNet reported that following  their anticipated reunion in February 2009, the show gained an average of 447,000 viewers.<ref name="447W">{{cite web|title=Why 'Y&R' is So Hot Right Now|url=http://sn.soapnet.go.com/news/article/why-yr-so-hot-right-now|work=[[SoapNet]]|publisher=([[The Walt Disney Company]])|accessdate=December 22, 2011}}</ref> Her romance with Adam has also gained a fan following, who call them 'Shadam' in social media.<ref name="e" /> The pairing have been perceived as "showing us the many shades of love. In this case, mostly dark" according to SoapNet.<ref name="dark">{{cite web|title=The Young and the Restless: Week in Review for 6/14/2010|url=http://sn.soapnet.go.com/news/article/the-young-and-the-restless-week-review-6142010?page=2,1|work=[[SoapNet]]|publisher=[[The Walt Disney Company]]|accessdate=December 24, 2011}}</ref> The show gained 115,000 viewers after they reunited in December 2010.<ref name="RHH">{{cite web|last=Giddens|first=Jamey|title=Ratings, Rants and Raves: Shadam Sex Better Than Viagra For Young and Restless Ratings|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2010/12/10/ratings-rants-and-raves-shadam-sex-better-than-viagra-for-young-and-restless-ratings|work=[[Zap2It]]|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|accessdate=August 24, 2012|date=December 10, 2010}}</ref> In 2012, Sharon's romance with Victor was the center of disapproval from the actors, critics and viewers. Of the relationship, journalist Michael Fairman said it "hasn<U+2019>t worked out or caught fire through the writing, or with the fans watching on-screen!"<ref>{{cite web|last=Bowe|first=Jillian|title=Eric Braeden on Young and Restless Twitter Drama: 'You Don<U+2019>t Do That to Fellow Colleagues'|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/08/29/eric-braeden-on-yr-twitter-drama-you-don%E2%80%99t-do-that-to-fellow-colleagues|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=September 6, 2012|date=August 29, 2012}}</ref> Several cast members have expressed their negative opinion about the relationship including Case, Braeden, Morrow and Muhney.<ref name="Crazy Talk" /><ref name="MSN" /><ref name="Joshy">{{cite web|last=Giddens|first=Jamey|title=Young and Restless' Joshua Morrow on 'Shictor': 'I Was Always Kind of Surprised That Nick Just Accepted This From His Dad'|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/08/23/young-and-restless-joshua-morrow-on-shictor-i-was-always-kind-of-surprised-that-nick-just|publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]]|work=[[Zap2It]]|accessdate=September 1, 2012|date=August 23, 2012}}</ref><ref name="Inside">{{cite web|last=Schaefer|first=Glen|title=Y&R star says show on <U+2018>cusp of change<U+2019> after writers axed|url=http://www.theprovince.com/star+says+show+cusp+change+after+writers+axed/7393387/story.html#ixzz29ZAoXuVV|work=[[The Province]]|publisher=[[Postmedia]]|accessdate=October 26, 2012|date=October 15, 2012}}</ref> Additionally, [[Daytime Confidential]] website placed Sharon and Victor atop their "Worst Soap Opera Couples" list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://daytimeconfidential.zap2it.com/2012/12/10/daytime-confidentials-10-worst-soap-opera-couples-of-2012?page=0,9 |last=Daytime Confidential |title=DC's 10 Worst Soap Opera Couples of 2012 |work=[[Zap2it]] |publisher=[[Tribune Media Services]] |date=December 21, 2012 |accessdate=December 22, 2012}}</ref>

===Accolades ===
Case has been honored with multiple accolades for her portrayal of Sharon. She received [[Daytime Emmy Award]] nominations in 1996 and 1997 for '[[Outstanding Younger Actress]]'.<ref name="a">{{cite web|title=Sharon Case (Cast Bio)|url=http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/show_guide/cast_bio_detail_1410.html|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20100815022725/http://www.theyoungandtherestless.com/show_guide/cast_bio_detail_1410.html|archivedate=Augusts 15, 2010|work=[[The Young and the Restless]]|publisher=[[Sony Pictures Entertainment]]|accessdate=December 22, 2011}}</ref> At the [[Soap Opera Digest|''Soap Opera Digest'' Awards]] in 1998, she won for "[[Soap Opera Digest Award for Hottest Female Star|Hottest Female Star]]" on a soap opera.<ref>{{cite web|title=Awards for 1998 <U+2013> Soap Opera Digest Award|url=http://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000616/1998|publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]|accessdate=December 22, 2011}}</ref> In 1999, she won a '[[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series]]', which was also her first time being nominated in that category.<ref name="a" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Lucci wins Daytime Emmy 19th Try (Full list of winners)|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=jNFHAAAAIBAJ&sjid=k38MAAAAIBAJ&pg=3031,2263630&dq=sharon+case+the+young+and+the+restless&hl=en|accessdate=December 22, 2011|newspaper=[[The Victoria Advocate]]|publisher=John M. Roberts|date=May 22, 1999}}</ref> Additionally, she was nominated in the same category in 2000 and 2004. At the 2003 ''Soap Opera Digest'' Awards, she received a nomination for 'Outstanding Supporting Actress'. Cassie's 2005 death storyline (and Sharon and Nicholas coping as parents afterwards) earned the show a [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Drama Series Writing Team]]. 'The death of Cassie Newman' is rated No. 41 on a list of 'The 100 Most Memorable Moments In Soap History', recognized by Soaps Hunks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soaphunks.net/moments.php?rank=041 |title=Shrine to the Soap Hunks: The 100 Most Memorable Moments in Soap History |publisher=Soaphunks.net |date= |accessdate=November 18, 2010}}</ref> Amid critical praise for Cassie's death storyline, Dan J. Kroll of ''Soap Central'' noted that it had "widely been expected" that Morrow and Case would receive nominations in the Outstanding Leading Actress and [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Drama Series|Actor]] categories at the [[33rd Daytime Emmy Awards]], which they were not. Despite this, Grimes did receive a nomination for Outstanding Younger Actress.<ref>{{cite web|last=J. Kroll|first=Dan|title=CBS Dominates Emmy Nominations; Y&R Tops Overall, GL Tops Acting Noms|url=http://soapcentral.com/emmys/news/2006/0208-emmy_noms.php|work=Soap Central|publisher=soapcentral.com|accessdate=February 11, 2013|date=February 8, 2006}}</ref> 

In January 2011, a Daytime Emmy award "Final push" by ''Canyon News'' suggested that her performance needed more "Emmy" attention.<ref>{{cite news|last=Garrett|first=Tommy|title=2011 Daytime Emmy Final Push|url=http://www.canyon-news.com/artman2/publish/Television/2011_Daytime_Emmy_Final_Push.php|accessdate=December 22, 2011|newspaper=Canyon News|date=January 30, 2011}}</ref> Case' performance in 2012, described as a "whirlwind year", was met with critical acclaim, due to writing by Bell that was criticized.<ref name="HwP" /> ''On-Air On-Soaps'' wrote: "Surviving probably one of the worst on-screen character assassinations in soap opera history, which virtually left viewers wondering, what the heck are the writers doing to the integrity of Sharon Newman, the once befallen heroine of Genoa City?, Case rebounded by making her performances noteworthy, no matter what the creative teams decided to do to her character".<ref name="HwP" /> This led ''Soap Opera Uncensored'' to name her "Entertainer of the Year" in January 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last=Branco|first=Nelson|title=Nelson Branco's Soap Opera Uncensored: Issue 59|url=https://www.smashwords.com/books/view/273469|accessdate=January 12, 2013}}</ref>

